The paper presents a new dataset for object recognition in the context of scene understanding, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The dataset was created with extensive crowd worker involvement, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also presents a statistical analysis of the dataset, which involves data mining and machine learning (cs.CL). Finally, the paper provides baseline performance analysis for detection results, which involves multimedia (cs.MM).
